    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yeah, I'll go ahead and un-assign myself for now\r\n\r\nFrom the error messages, it looks like we are using the right selectors for checking whether something is on screen. We're using the version that waits a little bit for something to load in, and is generally more fault-tolerant\r\n\r\nBut the fact that it's _still_ timing out despite that makes me think that either we have some bad UI rendering performance, or there's something wonky in the logic that is causing things to load in inconsistently. It's probably going to require a good bit of digging to find the root cause, though",
